    "department": "Services",
    "description": "LIFE AT UIPATH\n\nThe people at UiPath believe in the transformative power of automation to change how the world works. We’re committed to creating category-leading enterprise software that unleashes that power.\n\nTo make that happen, we need people who are curious, self-propelled, generous, and genuine. People who love being part of a fast-moving, fast-thinking growth company. And people who care—about each other, about UiPath, and about our larger purpose.\n\nCould that be you?\n\n\nYOUR MISSION\n\nWe are looking for an Test Engineer with hands-on experience testing UiPath workflows, AI/ML components, and Agentic automation systems. Your role will ensure robust quality across automation pipelines, particularly those enhanced by Python, GenAI, and non-deterministic ML models.\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL DO AT UIPATH\n\n - Design and maintain scalable, reusable test automation frameworks using UiPath Testing Platform\n\n - Create automated test scripts to validate end-to-end functionality, API integrations, UI Automation and workflow processes\n\n - Configure and deploy test bots using UiPath automation tools to simulate user interactions and system testing\n\n - Execute automated test scenarios and analyze results to identify defects or inconsistencies.\n\n - Monitor test robots within UiPath Test Manager and UiPath Test Cloud environments to ensure optimal performance.\n\n - Generate detailed test execution reports and track issues using UiPath Insights, defect management tools and ALM (Application Life Cycle Management) tools\n\n - Work closely with business analysts, product managers, test manager to define test requirements and validate outcomes\n\n - Contribute to the continuous improvement of testing frameworks, standards, workflows, and collaborative processes\n\n - Proactively Identify bottlenecks, challenges and potential product improvements and recommend optimizations to improve system efficiency, stability and scalability\n\n - Develop and execute testing strategies, test plans and use cases for UiPath automations.\n\n - Validate Python integrations and Document Understanding accuracy.\n\n - Automate test scripts and apply AI-assisted QA where applicable.\n\n - Perform functional, regression, smoke, and exploratory testing for Agentic workflows.\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL BRING TO THE TEAM\n\n - 3+ years of automation testing experience\n\n - Experience creating test automation frameworks\n\n - Exposure to testing AI/ML-driven and non-deterministic automations.\n\n - Familiarity with Python, C#, VB.NET for scripting and data driven testing.\n\n - Experience with test automation tools and AI-based QA platforms is a plus.\n\nNice to have:\n\n - Experience with RPA testing using UiPath\n\n - UiPath certifications such as \"UiPath Test Suite Developer\" or \"UiPath Certified Advanced RPA Developer (UiARD).\" or UiPath Software Testing Engineer Professional or UiPath Automation Developer Professional\n\n - Experience in robotic process automation (RPA) and its application in testing workflows.\n\n - Knowledge of Selenium, Appium, or other complementary test automation frameworks and tools that use Python and/or C#\n\nMaybe you don’t tick all the boxes above—but still think you’d be great for the job? Go ahead, apply anyway. Please. Because we know that experience comes in all shapes and sizes—and passion can’t be learned.\n\nMany of our roles allow for flexibility in when and where work gets done. Depending on the needs of the business and the role, the number of hybrid, office-based, and remote workers will vary from team to team. Applications are assessed on a rolling basis and there is no fixed deadline for this requisition. The application window may change depending on the volume of applications received or may close immediately if a qualified candidate is selected.\n\nWe value a range of diverse backgrounds, experiences and ideas. We pride ourselves on our diversity and inclusive workplace that provides equal opportunities to all persons regardless of age, race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, and expression, national origin, disability, neurodiversity, military and/or veteran status, or any other protected classes. Additionally, UiPath provides reasonable accommodations for candidates on request and respects applicants' privacy rights. To review these and other legal disclosures, visit our privacy policy https://www.uipath.com/legal/trust-and-security/privacy-policy.",
